(A) Is responsible to provide a fair start for each race.
S/he may appoint assistants, but assistants may not handle or take charge of a horse in the starting gate except by the expresspermission of the starter; (B) Shall report violations of these rules occurring in the starting of a race to the stewards; (C) Shall report immediately to the stewards when a door of the starting gate fails to open as the starter dispatches the field.
